source.class:
Class PDLOverrideSupported is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that expresses the printer's ability to attempt to override processing instructions embedded in documents' print data with processing instructions specified as attributes outside the print data.

IPP Compatibility: The category name returned by getName() is the IPP attribute name. The enumeration's integer value is the IPP enum value. The toString() method returns the IPP string representation of the attribute value.

Alan Kaminsky The printer makes no attempt to make the external job attribute values take precedence over embedded instructions in the documents' print data. The printer attempts to make the external job attribute values take precedence over embedded instructions in the documents' print data, however there is no guarantee. Construct a new PDL override supported enumeration value with the given integer value. value Integer value. Returns the string table for class PDLOverrideSupported. Returns the enumeration value table for class PDLOverrideSupported. Get the printing attribute class which is to be used as the "category" for this printing attribute value.

For class PDLOverrideSupported and any vendor-defined subclasses, the category is class PDLOverrideSupported itself. Printing attribute class (category), an instance of class{@link java.lang.Class java.lang.Class}.
